Optimization Approach:

ğŸ”¸ MILP (Mixed-Integer Linear Programming) Formulation:

Three strategies compared:

1. Minimizing bandwidth consumption â†’ Saves network resources.


2. Minimizing service provisioning cost â†’ Reduces expenses.


3. Minimizing VNF migrations â†’ Ensures stability and efficiency.




ğŸ”¸ Heuristic Algorithm:

Faster than MILP for large-scale networks.

Prioritizes minimizing VNF migrations to maintain service quality.



---

Findings:

ğŸ“ MILP-based methods are effective but take longer to compute.
ğŸ“ Heuristic algorithm provides near-optimal performance in significantly less time.
ğŸ“ Minimizing VNF migrations results in a more stable network and better user experience.
ğŸ“ Balancing network utilization across DU, CU, and 5GC is key to improving efficiency.

ğŸ“Œ Advantage Over Previous Papers:
âœ… Considers entire 5G slice orchestration, including RAN (gNBs) and Core Network.
âœ… Optimizes both bandwidth and computing resource allocation.
âœ… Uses advanced heuristics to scale better than MILP-only approaches.


